    "title": "Transistor Switch",
    "description": "Press and hold the tact button: USB → 10kΩ → NPN base (west) turns the transistor on. The collector branch (USB → 470Ω → red LED → north, emitter → ground on south) carries the LED current. Compare lesson 8 (button feeds the LED directly) and lesson 16 (pot threshold). B, C, and E labels match the standard NPN symbol."
